        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 11:47AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1146 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Portage, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Vicksburg...
Schoolcraft...         Scotts...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
